prompt_update_raw:
{
  "updated_prompt": "Given `question` and `summary_1`, produce one compact BM25-style search query (a single-line keyword query, not an explanation). Be conservative and reversible: preserve all named entities, titles, aliases, dates, relation words, and any uncertainty markers exactly as they appear in the inputs; do NOT introduce new entities, facts, or answer candidates. Prioritize missing-support recovery: if summary_1 signals a missing exact value or gap (e.g., exact release date, birth date/year, 2017 population, final issue year, which corporation was served), include the entity plus a focused relation term that targets that missing evidence (e.g., release date, date of birth, population 2017, final issue year, opened to serve). If summary_1 shows ambiguity between candidates, explicitly include the candidate set or a disambiguator present in summary_1 (e.g., location, role, parent administrative area, album title in parentheses). Keep the query compact: keep essential anchors and add or restore only the relation words needed to retrieve the support page; remove irrelevant verbosity. Output rules: produce only the query line; use concrete names/titles/aliases and relation keywords from the inputs; retain uncertainty words if present; avoid web-search operators, Boolean programs, or inventing facts.",
  "rationale": "Make the second-hop queries explicitly target the missing support noted in summary_1 by adding concise relation terms and disambiguators while preserving entities and uncertainty. This conservative, behavior-level update encourages retrieval of the specific support page without inventing facts or using search-operator syntax."
}
